#week-title("Three", "Major Configurations & The Saturn–Jupiter Cycle")

=== Core Teaching

Beyond the daily cycle of planetary hours, certain large-scale astronomical
configurations carry unusual weight for the Adept's mineral work. These are
not common occurrences — they mark significant thresholds in the Work's larger
arc.

*The Saturn–Jupiter conjunction (approximately every 20 years)* has been
regarded by the tradition as one of the most significant timing events for
the Great Work. The two social planets — Saturn as the principle of limitation
and structure (Binah), Jupiter as the principle of expansion and multiplication
(Chesed) — meeting in conjunction marks a threshold where the Work's
foundational structure and its expansive potential align. Historical alchemical
texts repeatedly reference the Saturn-Jupiter conjunction as an auspicious
moment for beginning a new major phase of the mineral work or for inaugurating
a new approach to the Stone.

The most recent such conjunction occurred in December 2020 (in Aquarius —
an air sign, suggesting a conjunction particularly favourable for the Mercury
principle and the gaseous, volatile aspects of the work). The next occurs in
October 2040.

*Saturn's return to its natal position* (approximately every 29.5 years) is
a threshold of personal maturation. The alchemist who has worked seriously
for 29 years and arrives at their Saturn return has, if they have maintained
the Work throughout, reached the moment when the structure of their practice
is tested: does it hold? Has it genuinely developed, or has it merely persisted
without evolution?

*The NDT Life Blueprint applied.* Javane and Bunker's *Numerology and the Divine
Triangle* provides a secondary system for mapping the practitioner's own
developmental cycles, independent of planetary cycles. Chapter 6's worked
example (Cayce's life) demonstrates how the life blueprint's period cycles
correspond to the themes of different phases of the Work. The practitioner
applies this to their own life blueprint as a parallel timing framework.

=== Topics This Week

- The Saturn–Jupiter conjunction: its significance and historical use
- Saturn return as personal maturation threshold
- Identifying current positions of Saturn and Jupiter relative to the natal chart
- The NDT life blueprint as a parallel timing system

